It’s always the start of December when I’m reminded how far Molly has come!
This time four years ago what started as a cold, led to a collapsed lung and she was helicoptered to Christchurch. It was such a horrible time, she had only been discharged from hospital after almost 5 months, one week earlier and next thing she was turning purple in our arms and we were told she might not make it. 
Up until she turned one she was so poorly all the time and so much smaller  than the others but she made up for it in sass and character. She still has a wheezy episodes often and can’t run far without bringing it on but it just seems to be part of life now. 
🌻

Deedee Day 🦋
Indie was home with me today and we got lots done together!
For her hard work helping me lux the car and pick up a few things from the supermarket we had lunch at a cafe. Then finally got her ear repierced after one fell out and she was even treated to getting her nails done which she has showed to anyone since! 
Although the whole day she was lost without any of her siblings home and kept asking me to pick up the other ‘twods’ from kindergarten. She also asked me for a new puppy. She knows I’m weak.

It was not easy for B to choose his new frames this year. He tried a lot on but none seemed just right in his own words. Finally he settled on these and when we opened them today he was stoked with the decision he made!

Seven sleeps till Christmas 🎄🎅🏼
No one is keen on Santa yet, maybe next year.

All set for Christmas.
Santa’s milk and cookies are set and his key is out 🍪🗝️
Magical seeds are planted ready for candy canes to grow 🍬
And the reindeer food is sprinkled on the lawn ✨

I’ve been meaning to split up the quads for awhile now. Ideally I would have split the quads Quinn & Indie sharing and Molly & Hudson sharing with B in his own room still. But Brooklyn has been asking to share with Hudson so boys and girls rooms it is! They are all stoked!
Sun, water, beers, friends. Just what I needed 🤍

First day back at kindergarten today!
Seven months and we will be swapping kindy clothes for school uniform.
🌸🦊🌻🦋

Felt brave and went for a walk to New World with the quads. I succumbed to peer pressure and let them all have a kids trolley and it went as well as you could expect. Hudson added in a bonus and came in red hot into the back of someone’s legs with the trolley😅
🌻🦊🦋🌸

Last day as a seven year old!
🦖

Happy Birthday to one of the best!
Love you B 🤍🦖

Four from four.
School checks passed ✅

After posting this in my stories I’ve had so many questions!
1. Why are they having them so early. I dont know about other towns but I assumed everyone was the same. From having multiple children I’ve learnt it’s not a simple pass for some children and I guess that it’s done early so that if a referral is need to be made, there’s time for the referral to be done and actioned before they start school. 
2. Why did all the quads pass when I’ve mentioned in the past there are a few issues. They all passed because any issues they have are already been looked after/in the process. Because they were born three months early they have been under paediatricians, speech and language, eyes and ears, the lot from the get go. There are some issues unresolved but because they are already in the system they passed.
3. The biggest question is Hudson. I’ve mentioned before he may not start school when the girls do. I’ve shared he has a diagnosis but I won’t share directly what it is as that’s his choice to share when he’s old enough to understand, not mine. I think people are confused why I would hold him back when he is clearly a lot further ahead academically than the girls. I would love Hudson to start with the girls but it comes down to safety and unfortunately sending him to school isn’t that simple right now. Hudson has no problem learning but it’s other aspects he struggles in and needs help with and unless we can get a good plan/strategies in place he will stay at kindergarten. Although a lot can change in six months so watch this space.

So proud of B and his effort in cross country today! 
🦖

Hudson’s been reading school books for a year now, next up is maths. Again he taught himself and I’m amazed at his speed. 
He’s a clever cookie 🍪 👨‍🎓 

And just for context I had the questions on a piece of paper in front of us, not the answers. Like my story i posted today.

EDIT - None of the other quads or Brooklyn wanted to play. 

It’s rugby season.
🌻

The twin bond is strong between these two! 👯‍♀️ 

I have so many messages lately asking if everything/everyone is ok as I haven’t been posting. I don’t have much of an answer except I just haven’t been on Instagram. Every time I think I’m busy, I just get busier and have little time to do much. So a little update. 
Everyone is fine! Molly and I both had our second round of covid a few weeks ago. All the other kids never tested positive but had the same symptoms. This one definitely got me worse than last year. The quads are very very excited about starting school in three months, they want to start tomorrow. However we still aren’t sure about Hudson, it’s a work in progress but regardless he’s such a happy wee boy, mostly always content on doing his own thing keeping busy. I can not believe they are almost 5 and Josh and I are about to plan a 5th birthday. I cant explain how fast time has gone. Netball season has started for me and so far so good! I’m really hoping I can play a lot more than I did last year after being so unwell. Indie is due to get her second round of grommets although it’s already been cancelled twice as she’s been sick. And Molly will be getting her tonsils and adenoids removed. All the girls have taken a huge interest in Dollie’s and doll houses lately which is perfect timing me for present inspo for their birthday but they have also stepped it up in sister wars and the bickering is testing sometimes. Brooklyns drawings are getting so good I’m so amazed at what he can do, but his ultimate goal in life is still to become a YouTuber. 

Over all everyone is good and happy.

Deedees surgeon done a fabulous job and so far so good, the finger is staying on! The blood supply caught on and she has a nice pink finger 🙌🏼
She will have another check up next week and in the mean time just lots of rest and staying away from doors 😅

Although you can’t take your eyes off Hudsy for a second, I love his free spirit and love for anyone and everything 🦊

Today we all went to chipmunks and he managed to slip away while I was distracted with the other kids and I found him in the party room sitting at the table eating a piece of cake 😅 We don’t know who’s party it was but we know it was a good cake. This was after he had already tried to join another party earlier on.

Three happy girls.
Deedee, Molls, Quinny
🦋🌻🌸

End of the rugby season for Molly 🏈 
The twins will definitely be playing as well next year, we will see how Hudsy goes.
They came running out of their room so excited to show me they were “twins!” 🌸🦋
Almost five years down and i still cant believe i have quadruplets 🤯

Hi 👋 

Ive had so many messages asking if everything is ok as I haven’t/dont post much anymore. 

Everything and everyone is fine! We are just busy and it never seems to end. With the quads turning 5 in a few weeks, there is lots to to do and seems to be taking over everything. 

We have been going to school visits and everything seems to be falling in place for Hudson which is such a relief 🤗 Watching them at school has been exciting. Quinn is in her element, Molly and Indie are super shy and Hudson has been showing off his maths skills. Although im excited for them, im also really sad that we are almost at this milestone already. As every parent knows, its just goes far too fast.

Winter has hit us all hard with bugs! And i got a bonus infection from a surgery i had early July. Indie is due for more grommets next week which im hoping goes ahead as it’s already been cancelled 3 times because shes been sick. Molly will also get her tonsils and adenoids removed soon. 

Brooklyn cant wait for the quads to start school, especially Hudson. He has made great progress at school so far this year and is always making me laugh with what he has to say. 

The girls got back from Joshs the other day and couldn’t wait to show me their new song. Hudson realises what he has to deal with from having three sisters and walks out and slams the door 😂

Everything 🖤
This time next week and the quads will be 5!

This is 5.

Happy Birthday to the coolest quadruplets i know!

🌸🦋🦊🌻

Thank you all for the birthday love for the quads yesterday!
They had such a good day and were very spoilt.
They are finishing off the week at kindy and they start school next Monday.

Thats a wrap on our Kindergartens days!
I cant even begin to say how amazing West End has been not only to Brooklyn, Quinn, Indie, Hudson and Molly, but also me! They have really looked after our whole family and went above and beyond and im so grateful they have been apart of their journey.

Finished off birthday week today ready to start school tomorrow!
🌻🌸🦊🦋

After a rough week of sickness, we were four from four and everyone was at school for the first time! Today was Indies first day and Quinn, Molly and Brooklyn have had a day or two off. 
Unfortunately I couldn’t be there as ive barely been out of bed since coming home from hospital but i have amazing family and friends around me to make it happen 🥰
Happy school days!!

So far so so so so good!!

🌸🦋🦊🌻

All excited for school mufti and disco day!! 🪩 

🦋🦊🦖🌸🌻

Made it through school holidays!!
Everyone was so patient with me over the last two weeks as i battled through sickness, so i treated them to the movies yesterday. Never would i ever thought i would take them all to the movies by myself so soon, but they did so well and loved the movie and the treats.
🦖🦊🌻🌸🦋

The girls started ballet today 🩰 
Indie, Molly & Quinn
🦋🌻🌸

As Deedee said “all the twods have a certificate now”

So proud of them all receiving a certificate for their own strengths since they have been at school. 

And even prouder of them all being so happy for each other. Today Indie was giving Quinn a thumbs up from where she was sitting 😍

💜 World Prematurity Day 💜

We always knew the quadruplets would be born premature, it was just a matter of when.

After going into spontaneous labour at 28.3 weeks, they were born at 28.4 weeks a couple hours after contractions started and there was no stopping it. We then started our NICU journey. 

Nothing can prepare you for living the NICU/premature ride. Its one thing getting used to all the alarms, seeing your baby covered in masks, wires, tubes and drains, but its another not being able to bond, care for or hold your baby while they are in an incubator.

There were many high highs and many low lows. One moment we would be celebrating a milestone with one baby and then in another we would be watching one baby’s heart stop and being resuscitated. 

Writing about it now brings back all of the emotions of how hard it was. I would constantly be walking from room to room, taking breaks to cry knowing i couldn’t give all my five children the attention, cuddles and love they needed. 

But overall i know how lucky we are. Although they were born so early and had normal premature complications, they are now happy and healthy 5 year olds which i credit all the doctors, nurses and hospitals that cared for them, and still do.

Three beautiful girls off to their ballet disco 🪩 
Indie, Quinn & Molly
🦋🌸🌻

Today was prize giving for Brooklyn and he received a certificate of merit!!

School can be challenging for Brooklyn. Academically he is fine however every other aspect can be a struggle especially socially. 

But to come away today one of four students to be recognised with an award and also given strives for excellence in maths, pe, science and reading, he has not stopped smiling since and says he’s looking forward to next year.

Same horse, different spot with a fresh coat of paint 🐴 

Quads 5, 4 and 2.

I know having quadruplets is wild but personally having identical twins is even crazier.
The quads share a bond and they know it themselves and i love watching them grow together, but Quinn and Indie are a next level. These two are always together giggling and playing. Despite being polar opposites, Quinn outgoing, stubborn, girly girl and Indie shy, sweet, cheeky, they compliment each other so well. Forever Quindie 🌸🦋
